      {
        "role": "All weight-700 uses: uppercase nav labels at 15px (ls 0.0530em), subheadings at 19px and 32px, link emphasis at 13px. Same family as body — the visual distinction is weight, not face change. letter-spacing: 0.0530em on uppercase nav",
        "sizes": "13px, 14px, 15px, 17px, 19px, 32px",
        "family": "duolingo-sans",
        "weight": "700",
        "lineHeight": "1.23, 1.21, 1.33, 1.40, 1.20",
        "letterSpacing": "0.0530em"
      }
    ],
    "description": "Duolingo's interface treats the page like a children's storybook: white paper canvas, chubby rounded display type, and a single saturated green that reads as 'correct answer' the moment it appears. Body copy stays calm in mid-gray so the green and its accent blue can do all the emotional work — green for progress and headings, blue for interactive links and secondary actions. Components are pill-shaped or chunky-rounded with thick 2px borders in black or color, giving every button the feel of a sticker pressed onto the page rather than a flat UI control.",
    "customSections": [
      {
        "title": "Agent Prompt Guide",
        "content": "Quick Color Reference:\n- text (heading): #58cc02\n- text (body): #777777\n- text (hero/heading dark): #4b4b4b\n- background (page): #ffffff\n- background (footer band): #58cc02\n- border (outlined button): #afafaf\n- accent (interactive link): #1cb0f6\n- primary action: no distinct CTA color\n\nExample Component Prompts:\nNo distinct primary action color was observed; use the extracted neutral button treatments instead of inventing a filled CTA color.\n3. Section Headline: feather 700 at 48px, line-height 1.2, letter-spacing -0.0200em, color #58cc02. Used for 'free. fun. effective.' and similar section titles.\n5. Body Paragraph: duolingo-sans 500 at 17px, line-height 1.18, color #777777, max-width ~480px to keep reading comfortable."
      }
    ]
